3. In its sales tax return for September 2004, as well as in its ZM for the third quarter of 2004, a Czech tax receipt of goods worth CZK 114,615 was issued to a German tax collector.
When reviewing the registration of the German tax collector in the MIAS system, the Czech financial official stated that this registration was only valid from 11 November 2004, and therefore after the goods were delivered to Germany.
The Czech tax collector issued a supplementary sales tax return in which he declared sales from domestic deliveries of CZK 114,615 and sales tax of CZK 21,777, which he paid.
In response to a request from the local FA in the Czech Republic, the NK found that the Czech tax authority subsequently filed an application to reopen the tax procedure in respect of the supplementary VAT return. As evidence, it submitted a confirmation from the German tax administration that the German tax authority had been registered since 1 January 2000.
